[
  {
    "udt_struct_v0": {
      "doc": "A dynamic state read the contract performs right before invoking the step.\\n\\nNeeded for DEXes whose swap args include state that changes ledger-by-ledger\\n(e.g. Sushi v3 `OracleHints`, some TWAP quotes). Fetching off-chain and\\npassing through the tx leaves a race window: another swap hitting the pool\\nin the same ledger invalidates the value and the inner tx reverts.\\n\\nWhen `prefetch` is `Some(pf)` the contract:\\n1. Calls `pf.target.invoke(pf.fn_name, pf.args)` \\xe2\\x80\\x94 usually a view method.\\n2. Replaces `step.args[pf.inject_at]` with the returned `Val`.\\n3. Also replaces `args[pf.inject_at]` in any `sub_auth` entry whose context\\ntargets the same `(step.target, step.fn_name)` \\xe2\\x80\\x94 so the authorize-as-\\ncurrent-contract entry stays byte-for-byte equal to the actual call.",
      "lib": "",
      "name": "Prefetch",
      "fields": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "args",
          "type_": {
            "vec": {
              "element_type": "val"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "fn_name",
          "type_": "symbol"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "inject_at",
          "type_": "u32"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "target",
          "type_": "address"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "udt_struct_v0": {
      "doc": "A single dynamic cross-contract call in the arbitrage route.\\n\\nThe bot builds each step with:\\n- `target` / `fn_name` / `args`: the exact sub-invocation to make\\n- `sub_auth`: the full `authorize_as_current_contract` tree this step needs\\n- `prefetch`: optional on-chain read whose result is spliced into `args`\\nand the matching `sub_auth` entry (see [`Prefetch`]).\\n\\nThe contract just pipes `sub_auth` through to the auth system \\xe2\\x80\\x94 no DEX-specific\\nknowledge on-chain. Per-DEX adapters on the bot side produce the correct\\n`sub_auth` trees for their respective call patterns (Aquarius direct pool,\\nSushi v3 with oracle hints, Soroswap UniV2 push-then-call, etc.).",
      "lib": "",
      "name": "SwapStep",
      "fields": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "args",
          "type_": {
            "vec": {
              "element_type": "val"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "fn_name",
          "type_": "symbol"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "prefetch",
          "type_": {
            "option": {
              "value_type": {
                "udt": {
                  "name": "Prefetch"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "sub_auth",
          "type_": {
            "vec": {
              "element_type": {
                "udt": {
                  "name": "InvokerContractAuthEntry"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "target",
          "type_": "address"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
